Package util.searchable

Interface ISearchFilter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ProductCategoryFilter, ProductCategoryNodeFilter, ProductNameFilter, TextSearchIgnoreCaseFilter
    public interface ISearchFilter
    This interface defines a search filter that allows to check whether two objects match or not ( searchFilterFunction(Object, Object)).
    Author:
    OOP

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      boolean searchFilterFunction​(Object originalObject, Object compareObject)
      Determines if an object matches a compare object using a filter function.

    • Method Detail

      • searchFilterFunction

        boolean searchFilterFunction​(Object originalObject,
                             Object compareObject)
        Determines if an object matches a compare object using a filter function. If one of the passed objects is null, the function will return false.
        Parameters:
        originalObject - the object that is to be checked
        compareObject - the object we compare against
        Returns:
        TRUE if the filter matches, FALSE otherwise
